{
  "text": "Excess weight and load on joints predispose patients with obesity to osteoarthritis [CITATION_1] . The literature suggests that chronic pain and obesity are linked comorbidities [CITATION_2] , adversely impacting each other [CITATION_3] . Obesity appears to be a risk factor for developing various pain diagnoses including headaches, lower back pain, fibromyalgia, abdominal pain, pelvic pain, and neuropathic pain [CITATION_4] . Weight loss for obese pain patients appears to be an important aspect of overall pain rehabilitation, although more research is needed to determine strategies to maintain long-term benefits [CITATION_5] .",
